                    Lo-Nyamship Cultural School
                    Est June 2014

                </p>

                <p class="text-left">
                    Lo-Nyamship Cultural School was established in June 2014 with the common interests of certain
                    members of the community. The need for community learning centers and cultural and language
                    preservation was necessary at the heat of the rising immigrant from the Himalayan regions of Nepal.
                    Community members informally discussed the importance of starting a program that will help children
                    of our community to come together as one in one space and take the progress from there.

                    <!-- More info -- opens more details -->
