                        <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
                            <div class="modal-content">
                                <div class="modal-header">
                                    <h5 class="modal-title" id="sundaySchoolHistory">Lo-nyamship Cultural School History
                                    </h5>
                                    <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
                                        <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
                                    </button>
                                </div>
                                <div class="modal-body">
                                    <!-- details -->
                                    <p>
                                        Lo-Nyamship Cultural School was established in June 2014 with the common
                                        interests of certain members of the community. The need for community learning
                                        centers and cultural and language preservation was necessary at the heat of the
                                        rising immigrant from the Himalayan regions of Nepal. Community members
                                        informally discussed the importance of starting a program that will help
                                        children of our community to come together as one in one space and take the
                                        progress from there. There was not any common space or program that could bind
                                        these newly arrived children from the homeland or children who were born and
                                        raised in a foreign land. Few people from the community raised the idea of
                                        starting a program where these children will come together, learn together and
                                        grow together with the same cultural, language and religious background. When
                                        Lo-Nyamship Cultural School started, Rapsang Bista, being the sole in charge and
                                        other members Pema Tsamdhu and ______ initiated the program right away with
                                        limited resources, logistic but with greater passion and commitment. The school
                                        was decided to run with parent committee members, volunteers and important
                                        members of the community. The terms of serving the school are two years for
                                        parents starting from Phakying and Losar. Parents will take turns alternatively
                                        starting either from Losar or Phyakying and will serve for two years.

                                    </p>
                                </div>
                                <div class="modal-footer">
                                    <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal">Close</button>
                                </div>
